From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fujisan Developer <fujisan@atari>
Date: Tue, 7 Apr 2026 00:00:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] netsio: gate SIO routing per-transaction via TransferToNetsio

Port the TransferToNetsio routing logic from Atari800MacX to fix
unconditional forwarding of all SIO traffic to FujiNet-PC.

Previously every SIO byte was sent to NetSIO whenever netsio_enabled was
set, including transactions for locally-mounted disk images.  FujiNet-PC
has no handler for those devices, so netsio_wait_for_sync() times out
and NetSIO_GetByte() blocks for up to 10 seconds on each such operation,
causing the observable slowness and hangs during FujiNet loading.

The fix inspects the first byte of each command frame (the device ID):
  - D1:-D8: (0x31-0x38) with a local disk mounted  -> handle locally
  - D1:-D8: with no local disk                      -> route to FujiNet
  - All other devices (N:, P:, R:, ...)             -> route to FujiNet

CMD line assertion (netsio_cmd_on) is deferred from
SIO_SwitchCommandFrame to SIO_PutByte so that it is only sent when the
transaction is actually destined for FujiNet-PC.  The CMD OFF sync wait
(netsio_cmd_off_sync + netsio_wait_for_sync) is similarly gated on
TransferToNetsio to avoid stalling after local-disk operations.

Based on Atari800MacX sio.c TransferToNetsio implementation.
---
 src/sio.c | 26 ++++++++++++++++++++------
 1 file changed, 20 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/sio.c b/src/sio.c
index 0000000..1111111 100644
--- a/src/sio.c
+++ b/src/sio.c
@@ -185,6 +185,7 @@ static int TransferStatus = SIO_NoFrame;
 static int ExpectedBytes = 0;
 #ifdef NETSIO
 int NetSIO_GetByte(void);
+static int TransferToNetsio = 0;
 #endif
 
 int ignore_header_writeprotect = FALSE;
@@ -1531,8 +1532,7 @@ void SIO_SwitchCommandFrame(int onoff)
 	if (onoff)
 	{				/* Enabled */
 #ifdef NETSIO
-		if (netsio_enabled && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
-			netsio_cmd_on();
+		TransferToNetsio = 0;
 #endif /* NETSIO */
 		if (TransferStatus != SIO_NoFrame) 
 #ifdef NETSIO
@@ -1548,7 +1548,7 @@ void SIO_SwitchCommandFrame(int onoff)
 	else
 	{
 #ifdef NETSIO
-		if (netsio_enabled && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
+		if (netsio_enabled && TransferToNetsio)
 		{
 			if (CommandIndex < ExpectedBytes)
 			{
@@ -1674,8 +1674,26 @@ void SIO_PutByte(int byte)
 #ifdef NETSIO
 	if (netsio_enabled && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
 	{
-		NetSIO_PutByte(byte);
-		return;
+		if (TransferStatus == SIO_CommandFrame && CommandIndex == 0) {
+			if (byte >= 0x31 && byte <= 0x38) {
+				int drive = byte - 0x31;
+				if (SIO_drive_status[drive] != SIO_OFF &&
+				    SIO_drive_status[drive] != SIO_NO_DISK)
+					TransferToNetsio = 0;
+				else
+					TransferToNetsio = 1;
+			} else {
+				TransferToNetsio = 1;
+			}
+			if (TransferToNetsio) {
+				netsio_cmd_on();
+				NetSIO_PutByte(byte);
+				return;
+			}
+		} else if (TransferToNetsio) {
+			NetSIO_PutByte(byte);
+			return;
+		}
 	}
 #endif /* NETSIO */
 	switch (TransferStatus) {
@@ -1832,7 +1850,7 @@ int SIO_GetByte(void)
 	int byte = 0;
 
 #ifdef NETSIO
-	if (netsio_enabled && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
+	if (netsio_enabled && TransferToNetsio && !BINLOAD_start_binloading)
 		return NetSIO_GetByte();
 #endif /* NETSIO */
 
